==English==

{{rank|provide|determined|month|820|news|prepared|support|bit}}

===Etymology===
Plural of obsolete noun "new", meaning "something that is new"; not, as is sometimes assumed, an acronym for "North, East, West, South" or anything else.

===Pronunciation===
*n(y)o͞oz, /n(j)uːz/, /<tt>n(j)u:z</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[gnu]]s (''depends on dialect'')
*:[[Rhymes:English:-uːz|Rhymes: -uːz]]

===Noun===
'''news''' (''[[uncountable]]'')

# New information of interest.
#: ''Is there any '''news''' about the storm?''
#: ''That's '''news''' to me.''
# Reports of current events broadcast via media such as newspapers or television.
#: ''Did you listen to the '''news''' tonight?''

